## Summary

### Files touched
- **Rewrote** `src/content/microcopy.ts` — new structured `microcopy` export organized by surface (`nav`, `buttons`, `errors`, `emptyStates`, `confirms`, `placeholders`, `meta`). Legacy `COPY` shape preserved as a thin compatibility shim sourced from `microcopy` so `src/_legacy_v1/dossier/ClassificationBanner.tsx` (a non-goal per §D) still compiles.
- **Added** `src/content/__tests__/microcopy.lint.test.ts` — vitest forbidden-words linter that walks every string + function-result in `microcopy`, asserts no banned word matches, asserts every required surface exists, asserts canonical buttons are lowercase, and asserts no stray exclamations outside the Unix-error convention.

### Components migrated to read from `microcopy`
`src/components/shell/`: SiteHeader, MobileDrawer, SkipLink, ThemeToggle, SiteFooter
`src/components/llm/`: ChatHeader, ChatInput, ChatMessageList, Message, RetryAffordance, ErrorBoundary, ChatSurface, useChat
`src/components/projects/`: ProjectsTable
`src/components/palette/`: Palette

### Strings centralized
`microcopy.ts` now houses **~80 visitor-facing strings/string-builders** spanning navigation labels, button labels, error/rate-limit messages, empty states, confirmation prompts, placeholders, ARIA labels, and meta strings (heading, subhead, persist toggle copy, classification labels, palette chrome, copyright).

### Acceptance results
- **B1 (single source)**: ✅ `microcopy.ts` is the canonical source; legacy `COPY` is a re-export shim.
- **B2 (voice)**: ✅ buttons (`ask`, `retry`, `clear`, `copy`, `copied`, `stop`, `prev`, `next`, `submit`, `reload`) are lowercase; prose/headings are sentence case; no exclamations outside the `! foo` Unix-error convention (verified by lint test).
- **B3 (migration scope)**: ✅ all active components that hard-coded chrome strings now import `microcopy`. Heuristic count `grep -nE '"[A-Za-z][^"]{2,40}"' src/components/ | grep -v _legacy_v1` dropped **1123 → 1098** (Δ = 25 chrome strings under the 41-char heuristic ceiling); the actual centralization is larger because longer strings (chat subhead, no-context note, validation copy, boundary detail) exceed the heuristic ceiling.
- **B4 (lint passes)**: ✅ `npx vitest run src/content/__tests__/microcopy.lint.test.ts` — 30/30 passing.
- **B5 (i18n-ready)**: ✅ keys are stable identifiers; values are strings or pure `(args) => string` functions, easily wrappable in a future `t()`.

